Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens-Schule Wyk auf Föhr Enthauptung eines  Heiligen" addressed (inside) to "Herrn Professor Dr. Hans Gerhard Evers 6101 Traisa b. Dst. Waldstrasse 43"

- Correspondence with Herbert Paulus about 'Tomyris and Cyrus' (dated 1955)
- Correspondence about the painting with a decapitation of a saint in Wyk auf Föhr (with V. Campenhausen dated 1967, with Pastor Eggers dated 1958, with H. Gerson dated 1951, with G. Gepts-Buysaert dated 1951, etc.)
- Photocopies of a reproduction of the painting with the decapitation of a saint
- Photos of the painting with the decapitation of a saint
- Bibliographic references
- Correspondence with Anneliese Schröder dated 1958
- Correspondence with Holzhausen dated 1951
- Small folder with a negative of the painting with a decapitation
